{"parse":{"title":"Conditional convergence","pageid":1198956,"revid":838849084,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>In <a href=\"/wiki/Mathematics\" title=\"Mathematics\">mathematics</a>, a <a href=\"/wiki/Series_(mathematics)\" title=\"Series (mathematics)\">series</a> or <a href=\"/wiki/Integral\" title=\"Integral\">integral</a> is said to be <b>conditionally convergent</b> if it converges, but it does not <a href=\"/wiki/Absolute_convergence\" title=\"Absolute convergence\">converge absolutely</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Definition\">Definition</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Conditional_convergence&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Definition\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>More precisely, a series <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle \\scriptstyle \\sum \\limits _{n=0}^{\\infty }a_{n}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mstyle displaystyle=\"false\" scriptlevel=\"1\">\n          <munderover>\n            <mo movablelimits=\"false\">&#x2211;<!-- \u2211 --></mo>\n            <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n              <mi>n</mi>\n              <mo>=</mo>\n              <mn>0</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n              <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#x221E;<!-- \u221e --></mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </munderover>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>a</mi>\n            <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n              <mi>n</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mstyle>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle \\scriptstyle \\sum \\limits _{n=0}^{\\infty }a_{n}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/cd74c3d82f5ce88655e1c0e3e8e8af56e62fce5e\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -2.005ex; width:4.728ex; height:4.509ex;\" alt=\"\\scriptstyle \\sum \\limits _{{n=0}}^{\\infty }a_{n}\"/></span> is said to <b>converge conditionally</b> if \n<span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle \\scriptstyle \\lim \\limits _{m\\rightarrow \\infty }\\,\\sum \\limits _{n=0}^{m}\\,a_{n}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mstyle displaystyle=\"false\" scriptlevel=\"1\">\n          <munder>\n            <mo form=\"prefix\">lim</mo>\n            <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n              <mi>m</mi>\n              <mo stretchy=\"false\">&#x2192;<!-- \u2192 --></mo>\n              <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#x221E;<!-- \u221e --></mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </munder>\n          <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\" />\n          <munderover>\n            <mo movablelimits=\"false\">&#x2211;<!-- \u2211 --></mo>\n            <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n              <mi>n</mi>\n              <mo>=</mo>\n              <mn>0</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n              <mi>m</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </munderover>\n          <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\" />\n          <msub>\n            <mi>a</mi>\n            <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n              <mi>n</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mstyle>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle \\scriptstyle \\lim \\limits _{m\\rightarrow \\infty }\\,\\sum \\limits _{n=0}^{m}\\,a_{n}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/b02d994cd4938e2e9c81d493dcd9d87087291aae\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -2.005ex; width:9.728ex; height:4.509ex;\" alt=\"\\scriptstyle \\lim \\limits _{{m\\rightarrow \\infty }}\\,\\sum \\limits _{{n=0}}^{m}\\,a_{n}\"/></span> exists and is a finite number (not &#8734; or &#8722;&#8734;), but <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle \\scriptstyle \\sum \\limits _{n=0}^{\\infty }\\left|a_{n}\\right|=\\infty .}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mstyle displaystyle=\"false\" scriptlevel=\"1\">\n          <munderover>\n            <mo movablelimits=\"false\">&#x2211;<!-- \u2211 --></mo>\n            <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n              <mi>n</mi>\n              <mo>=</mo>\n              <mn>0</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n              <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#x221E;<!-- \u221e --></mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </munderover>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>|</mo>\n            <msub>\n              <mi>a</mi>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <mi>n</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n            <mo>|</mo>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#x221E;<!-- \u221e --></mi>\n          <mo>.</mo>\n        </mstyle>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle \\scriptstyle \\sum \\limits _{n=0}^{\\infty }\\left|a_{n}\\right|=\\infty .}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/e905a8c7f8e2f4fe6c132d0c3dd72a7b32a69d39\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -2.005ex; width:8.634ex; height:4.509ex;\" alt=\"\\scriptstyle \\sum \\limits _{{n=0}}^{\\infty }\\left|a_{n}\\right|=\\infty .\"/></span>\n</p><p>A classic example is the <a href=\"/wiki/Alternating_series\" title=\"Alternating series\">alternating series</a> given by\n</p>\n<dl><dd><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle 1-{1 \\over 2}+{1 \\over 3}-{1 \\over 4}+{1 \\over 5}-\\cdots =\\sum \\limits _{n=1}^{\\infty }{(-1)^{n+1} \\over n}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n            <mn>3</mn>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n            <mn>4</mn>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n            <mn>5</mn>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n        <mo>&#x22EF;<!-- \u22ef --></mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <munderover>\n          <mo movablelimits=\"false\">&#x2211;<!-- \u2211 --></mo>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n            <mo>=</mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#x221E;<!-- \u221e --></mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </munderover>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <msup>\n                <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n                <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                  <mo>+</mo>\n                  <mn>1</mn>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n            </mrow>\n            <mi>n</mi>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle 1-{1 \\over 2}+{1 \\over 3}-{1 \\over 4}+{1 \\over 5}-\\cdots =\\sum \\limits _{n=1}^{\\infty }{(-1)^{n+1} \\over n}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/c43a308ba0d01080f3c91cc3f8845124f5728204\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -3.005ex; width:41.858ex; height:7.009ex;\" alt=\"1-{1 \\over 2}+{1 \\over 3}-{1 \\over 4}+{1 \\over 5}-\\cdots =\\sum \\limits _{{n=1}}^{\\infty }{(-1)^{{n+1}} \\over n}\"/></span></dd></dl>\n<p>which converges to  <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle \\ln(2)}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mi>ln</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2061;<!-- \u2061 --></mo>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle \\ln(2)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/bee3c8a0344afcd9379a7e528be216a029e8f348\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:4.911ex; height:2.843ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle \\ln(2)}\"/></span>, but is not absolutely convergent (see <a href=\"/wiki/Harmonic_series_(mathematics)\" title=\"Harmonic series (mathematics)\">Harmonic series</a>).\n</p><p><a href=\"/wiki/Bernhard_Riemann\" title=\"Bernhard Riemann\">Bernhard Riemann</a> proved that a conditionally convergent series of real numbers may be rearranged to converge to any value at all, including &#8734; or &#8722;&#8734;; see <i><a href=\"/wiki/Riemann_series_theorem\" title=\"Riemann series theorem\">Riemann series theorem</a></i>. The <a href=\"/wiki/L%C3%A9vy%E2%80%93Steinitz_theorem\" title=\"L\u00e9vy\u2013Steinitz theorem\">L\u00e9vy\u2013Steinitz theorem</a> identifies the set of values to which a series of terms in <b>R</b><sup><i>n</i></sup> can converge.\n</p><p>A typical conditionally convergent integral is that on the non-negative real axis of <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle \\sin(x^{2})}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mi>sin</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2061;<!-- \u2061 --></mo>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle \\sin(x^{2})}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/625aa9623450c5d654d1397ca591decc82773083\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:7.049ex; height:3.176ex;\" alt=\"\\sin(x^{2})\"/></span> (see <a href=\"/wiki/Fresnel_integral\" title=\"Fresnel integral\">Fresnel integral</a>).\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Conditional_convergence&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Absolute_convergence\" title=\"Absolute convergence\">Absolute convergence</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Unconditional_convergence\" title=\"Unconditional convergence\">Unconditional convergence</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Conditional_convergence&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Walter Rudin, <i>Principles of Mathematical Analysis</i> (McGraw-Hill: New York, 1964).</li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1290\nCached time: 20180908215712\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.016 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.051 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 51/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 0/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 216/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    0.000      1 -total\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache:idhash:1198956-0!canonical!math=5 and timestamp 20180908215711 and revision id 838849084\n -->\n</div>"},"langlinks":[{"lang":"bs","url":"https://bs.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uslovna_konvergencija","langname":"Bosnian","autonym":"bosanski","*":"Uslovna konvergencija"},{"lang":"ca","url":"https://ca.wikipedia.org/wiki/Converg%C3%A8ncia_condicional","langname":"Catalan","autonym":"catal\u00e0","*":"Converg\u00e8ncia condicional"},{"lang":"he","url":"https://he.wikipedia.org/wiki/%D7%94%D7%AA%D7%9B%D7%A0%D7%A1%D7%95%D7%AA_%D7%91%D7%AA%D7%A0%D7%90%D7%99","langname":"Hebrew","autonym":"\u05e2\u05d1\u05e8\u05d9\u05ea","*":"\u05d4\u05ea\u05db\u05e0\u05e1\u05d5\u05ea \u05d1\u05ea\u05e0\u05d0\u05d9"},{"lang":"nl","url":"https://nl.wikipedia.org/wiki/Voorwaardelijke_convergentie","langname":"Dutch","autonym":"Nederlands","*":"Voorwaardelijke convergentie"},{"lang":"ja","url":"https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E6%9D%A1%E4%BB%B6%E5%8F%8E%E6%9D%9F","langname":"Japanese","autonym":"\u65e5\u672c\u8a9e","*":"\u6761\u4ef6\u53ce\u675f"},{"lang":"ru","url":"https://ru.wikipedia.org/wiki/%D0%A3%D1%81%D0%BB%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%BD%D0%B0%D1%8F_%D1%81%D1%85%D0%BE%D0%B4%D0%B8%D0%BC%D0%BE%D1%81%D1%82%D1%8C","langname":"Russian","autonym":"\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439","*":"\u0423\u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0441\u0445\u043e\u0434\u0438\u043c\u043e\u0441\u0442\u044c"},{"lang":"sv","url":"https://sv.wikipedia.org/wiki/Betingad_konvergens","langname":"Swedish","autonym":"svenska","*":"Betingad konvergens"},{"lang":"uk","url":"https://uk.wikipedia.org/wiki/%D0%A3%D0%BC%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%BD%D0%B0_%D0%B7%D0%B1%D1%96%D0%B6%D0%BD%D1%96%D1%81%D1%82%D1%8C","langname":"Ukrainian","autonym":"\u0443\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0430","*":"\u0423\u043c\u043e\u0432\u043d\u0430 \u0437\u0431\u0456\u0436\u043d\u0456\u0441\u0442\u044c"},{"lang":"zh","url":"https://zh.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E6%9D%A1%E4%BB%B6%E6%94%B6%E6%95%9B","langname":"Chinese","autonym":"\u4e2d\u6587","*":"\u6761\u4ef6\u6536\u655b"}],"categories":[{"sortkey":"","*":"Mathematical_series"},{"sortkey":"","*":"Integral_calculus"},{"sortkey":"","*":"Convergence_(mathematics)"},{"sortkey"